FBIS4-12502 "drnes069dd_94006" FBIS-NES-94-069 Daily Report 9 Apr 1994 Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat Adviser Reponds to Peres' Afula Remarks 'Arafat Adviser Reponds to Peres' Afula Remarks LD1004080194 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 9 Apr 94 LD1004080194 Algiers Voice of Palestine Arabic BFN [Text] Brother Marwan Kanafani, adviser to brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], president of the state of Palestine and chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, made the following statement: It is very strange to hear this kind of logic from Shimon Peres, Israeli foreign affairs minister, especially because neither he nor Prime Minister Rabin have expressed any kind of regret and condemnation when the Israeli army and intelligence deliberately assassinated six young leaders from the Fatah Movement in Gaza recently. On the contrary, the Israeli housing minister expressed his appreciation and that of the government and the Israeli army for this kind of terrorist act immediately after the weekly meeting of the Israeli cabinet.
